{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
Some commentators place the obligation to obey the law and the organizational documents and policies under a third duty unique to charity fiduciaries--the \u8220\'3fduty of obedience.\rquote  Substantively, to these commentators, such a duty embraces a faithfulness to the purposes of the charity. These Principles, however, do not employ the terminology of a duty of obedience. While the members of the governing board must adhere to the organizational documents, they also have the obligation to keep the purpose of the charity current and useful. Accordingly, the board must amend the stated purposes when necessary and appropriate to do so, in accordance with the law and the existing organizational documents.
}
