132
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 However, because the third amendment to charter purposes (which broadly authorized the corporation to promote the health of the general public) exceeded the purposes of the affiliated trust, the court held that the board \u8220\'3fwill violate their fiduciary duties to those donors if they apply to the third, new purpose any proceeds of the sale attributable to donations from the ... trust and from unrestricted donations made\u8221\'3f before the amendment.
