{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F139398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
139
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EOPAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EOPAI_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The court embraced the rule that \u8220\'3fall the assets of a corporation organized solely for charitable purposes must be deemed to be impressed with a charitable trust by virtue of the express declaration of the corporation\rquote s purposes,\u8221\'3f notwithstanding that donors had not explicitly incorporated such purposes in gift instruments.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F140398601898_ID0E6PAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F140398601898_ID0E6PAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F140398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
140
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The court then focused on the precise language of the nonprofit\rquote s charter purposes. It observed that the articles of incorporation named the entity as a \u8220\'3fhospital\u8221\'3f and that, although the articles referred to multiple purposes, \u8220\'3fthe framework of those multiple purposes is the operation of a hospital.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F141398601898_ID0EQQAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F141398601898_ID0EQQAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F141398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
141
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 In summary, the court found that \u8220\'3f[f]he articles of incorporation alone--without resort to additional evidence--compel the inference that although Queen is entitled to do many things besides operating a 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_1530_940_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_1530_940_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*940
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 hospital, essential to all those other activities is the continued operation of a hospital.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F142398601898_ID0EDRAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F142398601898_ID0EDRAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F142398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
142
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 In short, the court held that although Queen could use some of its assets to further non-hospital-related purposes, it may not \u8220\'3fcease to perform the primary purpose for which it was organized.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F143398601898_ID0EQRAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F143398601898_ID0EQRAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F143398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
143
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EXRAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EXRAI_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Queen of Angels
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 is consistent with older California cases
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F144398601898_ID0EFSAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F144398601898_ID0EFSAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F144398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
144
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 that continue to influence some judges in other jurisdictions.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F145398601898_ID0EKSAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F145398601898_ID0EKSAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F145398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
145
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Whether these cases remain controlling under California law has been questioned, insofar as they pre-date the 1980 enactment of California\rquote s nonprofit corporation act.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F146398601898_ID0EPSAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F146398601898_ID0EPSAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F146398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
146
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 However, the California Attorney General continues to embrace the trust law analysis in these cases,
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F147398601898_ID0ESSAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F147398601898_ID0ESSAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F147398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
147
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 as do some attorneys general in other states.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F148398601898_ID0EWSAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F148398601898_ID0EWSAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F148398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
148
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0E4SAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0E4SAI_1}
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa200 \sb200 
c. Case Law Supporting the Dynamic Charter Fidelity Norm
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EHTAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EHTAI_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Consistent with the PLNO, and contrary to the approach of 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Manhattan Eye, Hahnemann Hospital
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, and 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Queen of Angels
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, some cases support or implicitly embrace the dynamic charter fidelity norm as applied to a charity\rquote s post-amendment use of assets held prior to an amendment to its articles of incorporation. For example, in 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Kansas East Conference of the United Methodist Church, Inc. v. Bethany Medical Center, Inc.
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, a Methodist conference of churches (\u8220\'3fthe Conference\u8221\'3f) sought a declaratory judgment and 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_1530_941_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_1530_941_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*941
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 an order to dissolve Bethany Medical Center, Inc. (\u8220\'3fBethany\u8221\'3f) and distribute its assets to the Conference.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F149398601898_ID0E1UAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F149398601898_ID0E1UAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F149398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
149
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Bethany held approximately $40-45 million in cash after it sold its hospital assets to a for-profit company.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F150398601898_ID0E6UAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F150398601898_ID0E6UAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F150398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
150
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 At the time of the litigation in question, Bethany\rquote s articles of incorporation permitted its board to amend them, and stated that upon dissolution, Bethany\rquote s net assets would be distributed to the Conference.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F151398601898_ID0EEVAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F151398601898_ID0EEVAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F151398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
151
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The lower court refused to order that Bethany be dissolved, but it did issue a permanent injunction prohibiting Bethany from displacing the Conference as the recipient of the assets if Bethany was dissolved.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F152398601898_ID0EIVAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F152398601898_ID0EIVAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F152398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
152
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EPVAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EPVAI_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The Kansas Supreme Court rejected the Conference\rquote s argument that charitable trust law, rather than the statutory language of the Kansas Corporation Code, should control the disposition of the case.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F153398601898_ID0EXVAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F153398601898_ID0EXVAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F153398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
153
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The court dismissed the notion that the Conference functioned \u8220\'3fas a trust settlor,\u8221\'3f and emphatically concluded that 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u8220\'3fdissolution of Bethany is governed by the corporate statutes.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F154398601898_ID0EFWAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F154398601898_ID0EFWAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F154398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
154
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Having rejected the application of trust law to the question of whether Bethany must be dissolved, the court then addressed the trial court\rquote s injunction against amending Bethany\rquote s articles so as to displace the Conference as the distributee of Bethany\rquote s assets in the event of Bethany\rquote s dissolution.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F155398601898_ID0EKWAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F155398601898_ID0EKWAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F155398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
155
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Bethany argued that the court violated its due process rights by entering the injunction without any notice or hearing on the issue.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F156398601898_ID0EPWAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F156398601898_ID0EPWAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F156398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
156
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Bethany\rquote s argument required proof that it possessed a legally-protected interest which it could not be deprived of without notice and an opportunity to be heard.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F157398601898_ID0EUWAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F157398601898_ID0EUWAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F157398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
157
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The Kansas Supreme Court accepted the argument that state nonprofit law created a property interest in Bethany,
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F158398601898_ID0EXWAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F158398601898_ID0EXWAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F158398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
158
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 and then linked its analysis rejecting the application of trust law to the question of the propriety of the lower court\rquote s injunction.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F159398601898_ID0E3WAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F159398601898_ID0E3WAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F159398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
159
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The court concluded that \u8220\'3fthe district court interfered in the internal affairs of Bethany by enjoining it from amending its 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_1530_942_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_1530_942_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*942
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 articles of incorporation as to the distribution of its assets upon dissolution.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F160398601898_ID0EPXAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F160398601898_ID0EPXAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F160398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
160
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Issuing the injunction, therefore, denied Bethany due process.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F161398601898_ID0ETXAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F161398601898_ID0ETXAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F161398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
161
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0E1XAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0E1XAI_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Bethany Medical Center
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 supports the dynamic charter fidelity norm in both its rationale and holding. The case rejects the notion that charitable trust law trumps state nonprofit statutes that confer power to a governing board to amend an entity\rquote s articles of incorporation and act accordingly.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F162398601898_ID0ENYAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F162398601898_ID0ENYAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F162398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
162
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Although the court considered the issue in the context of preserving the right of directors to amend the entity\rquote s dissolution clause (and thereby redirect the disposition of corporate assets upon dissolution) the rationale of the case would also apply to the right of directors to amend an entity\rquote s purposes clause, and thereby redirect the use of corporate assets in daily operations.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F163398601898_ID0ERYAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F163398601898_ID0ERYAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F163398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
163
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EYYAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EYYAI_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Another case that broadly supports the dynamic charter fidelity norm is 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Dodge v. Trustees of Randolph-Macon Woman\rquote s College
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F164398601898_ID0EJZAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F164398601898_ID0EJZAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F164398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
164
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 In this case, the plaintiffs brought suit to enjoin the Randolph-Macon Woman\rquote s College (\u8220\'3fthe College\u8221\'3f), a single-sex liberal arts college, from implementing its plan to become co-educational.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F165398601898_ID0EOZAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F165398601898_ID0EOZAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F165398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
165
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The College sought to amend its articles of incorporation to include men and women, and planned to sell assets, including its art collection, to finance campus alterations that would facilitate the transition to a co-educational institution.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F166398601898_ID0ETZAI_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F166398601898_ID0ETZAI_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F166398601898_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
166
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
