{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Under this theory, the court concluded that distributions in liquidation were governed by a statutory dissolution provision applicable to \u8220\'3f[a]ssets received and held by the corporation subject to limitations permitting their use only for charitable, religious, eleemosynary, benevolent, educational or similar purposes.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
