264
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 but there is no obvious reason to bind them to the historic mission fidelity norm when trust purposes are broadly phrased. Nonetheless, if a charitable trust has broadly phrased purposes, holding its trustees to the dynamic mission fidelity norm would likely enhance efficiency.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
