Additional protection of donors\rquote  reliance interests could take the form of requiring a charitable corporation to notify the state attorney general of a proposed charter amendment or other significant change. The attorney general could then petition a court for an injunction if he or she believes the change is improper. Such an approach approximates adoption of the static or historic fidelity norms, insofar as a governmental actor (the state attorney general) functionally has the power through adjudication to ensure that a change will become effective only if another governmental actor, a court, permits it. Some states essentially follow this approach in certain contexts. 
